headline: What Does the $1.69B UK Investment Mean for PayPal’s Share Price in 2025?
summary: If you have been watching PayPal Holdings lately and wondering whether now is the time to buy, hold, or take your gains, you are definitely not alone. After all, its story has felt like a rollercoaster, and the numbers only reinforce the feeling. In just the last seven days, shares have edged up 2.0%, but over the last year they are down over 11%. Stretch that horizon to five years, and PayPal has tumbled 63.6%, leaving some long-term holders shaking their heads and others eyeing a potential...
